EnvironmentSettings
EnvironmentSettings

Gets or sets a list of environment variable settings for the Job Release task.
Id
Id

Gets or sets a string that uniquely identifies the Job Release task within the job.
MaxWallClockTime
MaxWallClockTime

Gets or sets the maximum elapsed time that the Job Release task may run on a given compute node, measured from the time the task starts. If the task does not complete within the time limit, the Batch service terminates it. The default value is 15 minutes. You may not specify a timeout longer than 15 minutes. If you do, the Batch service rejects it with an error; if you are calling the REST API directly, the HTTP status code is 400 (Bad Request).
ResourceFiles
ResourceFiles

Gets or sets a list of files that the Batch service will download to the compute node before running the command line.
RetentionTime
RetentionTime

Gets or sets the minimum time to retain the task directory for the Job Release task on the compute node. After this time, the Batch service may delete the task directory and all its contents.
UserIdentity
UserIdentity

Gets or sets the user identity under which the Job Release task runs.

    Gets or sets the command line of the Job Release task.

    public string CommandLine { get; set; }Public Property CommandLine As String

    Property Value

    • String
      String

    Remarks

    The command line does not run under a shell, and therefore cannot take advantage of shell features such as environment variable expansion. If you want to take advantage of such features, you should invoke the shell in the command line, for example using "cmd /c MyCommand" in Windows or "/bin/sh -c MyCommand" in Linux.

    Id
    Id

    Gets or sets a string that uniquely identifies the Job Release task within the job.

    public string Id { get; set; }Public Property Id As String

    Property Value

    • String
      String

    Remarks

    The ID can contain any combination of alphanumeric characters including hyphens and underscores and cannot contain more than 64 characters. If you do not specify this property, the Batch service assigns a default value of 'jobrelease'. No other task in the job can have the same id as the Job Release task. If you try to submit a task with the same id, the Batch service rejects the request with error code TaskIdSameAsJobReleaseTask; if you are calling the REST API directly, the HTTP status code is 409 (Conflict).
